Tappa Keyboards Privacy Policy
Back to Trust Center
Introduction
Tappa Keyboards (“Tappa”, “We”, “us”, or “our”) is a privacy-first mobile device technology development company that specializes in offering end users (“Users” or “You”) the best-in-class experience in a mobile keyboard application. We believe in creating immersive mobile-first environments where people can connect with the brands they love. This is facilitated through a combination of technology solutions that have user privacy at its core without compromising the user experience. Tappa cares about the security and privacy of the personal data that is entrusted to us. We believe the user should not have to compromise privacy for functionality.
It is Tappa’s policy to respect your privacy while you use our platforms (“the Tappa Keyboards”), published by Tappa Operations Inc., Lemur Labs SRL, 2024 Themes and Keyboards, which we own and/or operate. Any information that we do receive is by fair and lawful means.
Tappa Keyboards recognizes that Users are mindful of their privacy. Tappa Keyboards provides this Privacy Policy to help you make an informed decision about whether to use or continue to use the Tappa Keyboards. If you do not agree to our practices, please do not use Tappa Keyboards and any other Keyboard applications we provide. Your continued use of the Tappa Keyboards will be regarded as acceptance of our privacy and personal information practices.
We offer Tappa Keyboards for both iOS and Android platforms and we refer to all these products, including future updates and upgrades as “Services” in this policy.
A Special Notice About Children
Users Under 16 Years of Age
are not eligible to use the Services unsupervised, and we ask that children do not submit any personal information to us. If you are under the age of 16, you may only use the Services in conjunction with, and under the supervision of your parents or guardians.
Users Under 13 Years of Age
Children under the age of 13 are not eligible to use the Services.  Only parents or legal guardians can submit personal information to us about a child.
By visiting our Site and/or using our Services, or by including children under the age of 13 years old in our provided services, you are agreeing to the terms of this Privacy Policy and the accompanying Terms of Use.
If we learn we have collected Personal Information from a User under the age of 13 without parental consent, we will delete that information as quickly as possible.
If you choose to use any of our AI-powered features, you must be over the age of 18.  For more information, check our
Terms of Service
.
Owner & Data Controller
Tappa Keyboards, a business brand of Tappa Operations Inc. 1216 Broadway, Office #202 New York, NY 10001. In regard to the processing of your data, Tappa Operations Inc. acts as the controller.
